    <div xml:id="PN330">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>vēntuṭait tāṉai muṉaikeṭa neritali</l>
<l>ṉēntuvāḷ valatta ṉoruva ṉākit</l>
<l>taṉṉiṟantu vārāmai vilakkaliṟ peruṅkaṭaṟ</l>
<l>kāḻi yaṉaiyaṉ mātō veṉṟum</l>
<l>pāṭic ceṉṟōrk kaṉṟiyum vārip</l>
<l>puraviṟ kāṟṟāc cīṟūrt</l>
<l>toṉmai cuṭṭiya vaṇmai yōṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Because of being crushed, so that the frontier crumbles, by the king’s army, (1)</l>
<l>being the one has strength in the sword he raises, (2)</l>
<l>when he resists so that they cannot get past him, is he not </l>
<l>like the force of the great sea, (3-4c)</l>
<l>‒ he of a generosity pointed out of old, (7)</l>
<l>from the little village that is unable of [enough] income </l>
<l>for the tax, apart from from being always sung by those who go? (4d-6)   </l>
</lg>
    </div>
